cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CL

The paper presents a methodology for eye tracking using mouse clicks, which is relevant to the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The methodology is evaluated on a variety of image types, including natural images and information visualizations, which suggests relevance to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of the methodology for ranking image and design elements, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) in terms of analyzing visual and textual content.
